{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Landowner filed petition for writ of certiorari, challenging decision of Board of County Commissioners approving developer\rquote s planned unit development project. The Circuit Court of Polk County, 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=h&pubNum=176284&cite=0146214801&originatingDoc=I192a63680dcf11d9821e9512eb7d7b26&refType=RQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf40 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Carolyn K. Fulmer
}}}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, J., dismissed, and landowner appealed. The District Court of Appeal, Scheb, Acting C.J., held that proper method for reviewing Board\rquote s decision was by way of certiorari, rather than injunctive or declaratory suit.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
