}\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ri30 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \ql \li30 \fs20 \intbl \cell \intbl 
{\ri30 \li30 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \ql \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb0 
County board of commissioners\rquote  approval of planned unit development project, over objection of landowner that developer\rquote s proposals did not meet minimum requirements specified in zoning ordinance as prerequisites for approval of planned unit development, was quasi-judicial action that was properly reviewed by way of certiorari, rather than by way of injunctive or declaratory suit; landowner was not contesting validity or applicability of underlying ordinance and board rendered its decision following de novo hearing.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf26 \f2 \ri30 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li30 
